-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Aamal of Qatar and Qatar Telecom
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2012-04-30T11:09:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-30/persian-gulf-stocks-dubai-islamic-bank-and-qatar-telecom.html
Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  fell
0.3 percent, the biggest drop since April 19, to 2,503.82 at the
2 p.m. close in the emirate. The  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  decreased 0.5
percent, while Qatar’s  QE Index (DSM)  rose 0.2 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Aamal Co. (AHCS)   of Qatar slumped the most in almost a
month, decreasing 3.4 percent to 16.9 riyals. The Qatar-based
diversified investment company said first-quarter profit fell to
54.6 million riyals ($15 million) from 59.1 million riyals a
year earlier.  Qatar Telecom  QSC (QTEL QD) advanced 1.5 percent to 140.1
riyals, the highest close since March 2008. The Persian Gulf
country’s biggest company by revenue posted a first-quarter
profit of 711.4 million riyals, beating estimates.  To contact the reporter on this story:
